The paper focuses on developing a data-driven auto-tuning framework for motion planners in autonomous driving vehicles. This involves using machine learning algorithms to optimize the reward/cost functional for Level-4 autonomous driving vehicles. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics and Control), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
